You can convert existing videos or make clips from those same existing videos with ffmpeg on linux, windows and android.

it's as simple as
ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -c:v libvpx-vp9 -b:v 2M -an output.webm

add -ss 00:01:00 -to 00:01:15 somewhere in the middle if you want to make clips from a larger video, you can specify just seconds, or even milliseconds if you prefer, I use mpv to get the millisecond counts for frame perfect clips.

If you wanna save space to stay under the 2MB esfores limit, remember that lowering the resolution with -vf "scale=-1:720" won't save disk space, lowering the fps with "-fps 15" definitely will, especially if you're converting from a 60fps source.
